@chetan51 please review

Now you can write docs in Markdown or reStructured Text and
give swagger a function to process docstrings. It could
look like that:

```python
import flask_swagger
import CommonMark

def process_doc(text):
    parser = CommonMark.DocParser()
    renderer = CommonMark.HTMLRenderer()
    ast = parser.parse(text)
    return renderer.render(ast)

@app.route("/docs/swagger.json")
def swagger_spec():
    spec = flask_swagger.swagger(app, process_doc=process_doc)
    return jsonify(spec)
```

- added a scope configuration stanza for flow routes
to configure interface-set communities
- both transitive and non transitive instance are supported

Example of configuration:
flow {
        route MYROUTE {
                match {
                        source 1.1.1.1/32;
                        destination 2.2.2.2/32;
                }
                scope {
                        interface-set [  transitive:input:3:3 non-transitive:output:12:1 transitive:input-output:1:1 ];
                }
                then {
                        accept;
                }
        }
}


